Season 2 strayed a bit from the noir aspect that was heavily focused on last season. In season 2 we get a few doses of sci-fi and superhero episodes, along with a parody of that awful reality show Big Brother. The creators went in a different direction. Maybe they were trying to reel in millennial viewers by getting with the times. I was put off by it. Modern genres can be lame. I Liked season 1 much better.
